<p>In the context of this problem, a false positive can be harmful to the sender, as it occurs when the model classifies a legitimate message as spam. This could result in missing important or urgent messages. Conversely, if our goal is to minimize this, we may allow some spam messages to go through. The Logistic Regression model performed excellently, with zero false positives and an overall accuracy of 0.98. Our Random Forest model also achieved great results, with no false positives and a general accuracy of 0.97.</p>
<p> We have successfully trained a useful and robust model to classify spam messages. </p>

